        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:53PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers over
southeastern Colorado Springs, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Fountain, Stratmoor, Fort Carson, Schriever Space
Force Base, Security, Security-Widefield, Falcon, Cimarron Hills,
Peterson Space Force Base, and Peyton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
